ROLAND GARROS
May 29, 2019
Juan Ignacio Londero
START_OF_INTERVIEW_TEXT








J. LONDERO/R. Gasquet
6-2, 3-6, 6-3, 6-4
THE MODERATOR: Questions in English, please.
Q. Can you talk about what it represents to be at this third round of Roland Garros?
JUAN IGNACIO LONDERO: It is a little bit like dreaming with my eyes open.  It was a very good match that I play today.
I don't have much to say.  I'm just really happy.  I know I will try to enjoy as much as I can the whole day.
Q. You play a lot of clay.  Maybe all your matches are on clay this year.  Why do you love it so much?
JUAN IGNACIO LONDERO: I've been playing on clay all my life.  I love it.  And I arranged a very good swing on clay court, and that's the surface that my tennis is based on.
Q. Do you know your next opponent?  Moutet?
JUAN IGNACIO LONDERO: I know him just by name.  I saw him in some tournaments.  I don't know very much how is his game.  I still need to analyze his game.






END_OF_INTERVIEW_TEXT